feed.entry.2.author.name.label: Nanchang Man
feed.entry.2.updated.label: 2023-03-22T16:18:12-07:00
feed.entry.2.title.label: Truly amazing.
feed.entry.2.content.label: This meditation app is nothing short of a positive and powerful life changer. It offers ways to help heal yourself in a world of stress and turmoil. It helps you to understand why you may feel anxiety/depression in your daily living and through meditation offers ways to address these and bring back hope and meaning to life. This isn‚Äôt just a small set of meditations to try but a whole range of ongoing teachings and challenges. The fact that the app is totally free is testament to the dedication, belief and hard work of a few volunteers in trying to bring a natural way of helping all of us to help ourselves develop happiness, compassion and purpose in everything we experience every day.

feed.entry.11.title.label: Changed my life!
feed.entry.11.content.label: I heard about meditation about a year ago, but always struggled to keep a consistent habit and didn‚Äôt really understand meditation and mindfulness. I thought if I had thoughts while meditating , I must be meditating wrong or I was just bad at meditation. Since I  downloaded  Medito 2 weeks ago, I have meditated every day. I also found it useful for the wide range of sessions from sleep to mindfulness to grief meditation and the daily meditation provides you with something new every day. I found it extremely useful to be able to do a short session of 3 minutes to help build up my meditation practice and the beginner courses have been very informative and relaxing as well as helping to grasp the basics of meditation. However, occasionally the servers go down so I would recommend downloading some sessions and turn your  phone onto airplane mode to see your downloaded sessions of the servers are down .
